ScholaRec INSTALLATION
======================

About
=====
This document specifies how to build, customize, and install 
ScholaRec for the first time. See RELEASE-NOTES if you 
are upgrading from a previous scholarec release.

Contents
========

0. Prerequisites
1. Quick instructions for the impatient scholarec users
2. Detailed instructions for the patient scholarec users/developers

--------------------------------------------------------------------

0. Prerequisites:

   Install the prerequisites through the following command:

   $ pip install -r requirements.txt --use-mirrors

   This software requires Python 2.7.5+ 
--------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Quick instructions for the impatient scholarec users:

   $ sudo sh setup.sh

--------------------------------------------------------------------

2. Detailed instructions for the patient scholarec users/developers:
   
   A) If you're a developer
      
      - Run the following on console:

      	$ git clone https://github.com/arcolife/scholarec.git
	$ cd scholarec/
	$ sudo sh setup.sh	
      	$ sudo python setup.py develop
     	$ ./tests/run-tests.sh
	$ ./tests/query_parse

   B) If you're a user

      - Run the following on console:
      	
	$ sudo sh setup.sh
     	$ ./tests/run-tests.sh
	$ ./tests/query_parse

--------------------------------------------------------------------